stepTitle: Adults aged $$18$$ years old and older were randomly selected for a survey on obesity. Adults are considered obese if their body mass index (BMI) is at least $$30$$. The researchers wanted to determine if the proportion of women who are obese in the south is less than the proportion of southern men who are obese. The results are shown in the table
choices: A lower proportion of southern women are obese compared to southern men
